article.headline: Mississippi State cruises to victory
article.story:
GAINESVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- LaToya Thomas had 22 points and 13
rebounds as Mississippi State (No. 12 ESPN/USA Today, No. 13 AP) pulled away in the second half
and beat reeling Florida 83-54 Sunday.

Mississippi State (16-4, 5-2 Southeastern Conference) led 37-32
at halftime, then blew the game open with a 40-10 second-half run.
Rebecca Kates tied her career-high with 19 points and Blessing
Chekwa added a career-best 17 for the Bulldogs.

It was the school-record eighth consecutive loss for Florida
(8-12, 0-7). All eight of the losses have come by at least 14
points. Vanessa Hayden led the Gators with 12 points, but foul
trouble limited her to 20 minutes.

Tan White sparked Mississippi State's second-half surge by
scoring nine straight points, making two 3-pointers and then
sinking three free throws after being fouled on another 3-point
attempt.

Kates added seven points during the decisive spurt, and Chekwa
scored four baskets in succession to make the score 79-48.

Hayden picked up her fourth foul with 14:48 remaining,
coinciding with the bulk of Mississippi State's second-half
outburst. After Hayden went to the bench, Florida made only one
field goal in the next seven minutes.

The win was Mississippi State's fifth in its last six games.

Florida coach Carolyn Peck used an all-freshman starting lineup
for the third straight game.
